## Methods (draft)

Differential transcript usage (DTU) analysis identified **{{ meta.gene }}** as showing
significant isoform switching in **{{ meta.cell_type }}** cells
(DIFFUSE Δ = {{ "%.3f"|format(stats.diffuse_delta) }}, DTU p = {{ "%.2e"|format(stats.dtu_p) }}).
The AD-associated isoform ({{ meta.ad_transcript_id }}, {{ sequences.ad_length }} aa)
was compared against the CT-predominant isoform ({{ meta.ct_transcript_id }},
{{ sequences.ct_length }} aa; length difference: {{ sequences.length_diff }} aa).
Protein domain annotation was performed using HMMER 3.3.2 hmmscan against
Pfam-A (release 36.0; E-value threshold 0.01). Motif analysis employed Eisenberg
hydrophobicity scale for MTS scoring (MitoFates criteria) and regex-based detection
for LYR, HHH, and kinesin catalytic motifs. Genomic coordinates were extracted from
SQANTI3 classification and GTF output. Repeat element annotation used the UCSC
RepeatMasker REST API (hg38).

